Arthur Rooke https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthur_Rooke 0 Arthur Rooke was a British actor and film director of the silent era. Rooke had worked in the theatre for many years before he went into films. He initially co-directed several films with A.E. Coleby, but later began directing films by himself. By the early 1920s he was one of the more successful British film directors. Arthur_Rooke was a_British_actor_and_film_director of the_silent_era .
